GNU Gama  can be found in the subdirectory @code{/gnu/gama/} on
your favourite FTP @uref{http://www.gnu.org/prep/ftp.html, GNU mirror} or
cloned from the GIT. See our project page at
@uref{http://savannah.gnu.org/projects/gama/, savannah} for more
information.

To get an anonymous read-only access to the GIT repository for the
latest GNU Gama source, issue the following command

@example
git clone git://git.sv.gnu.org/gama.git
@end example


@noindent The collection of sample networks is available separetely. To clone
the @code{gama-local} examples from GIT use the command

@example
git clone git://git.sv.gnu.org/gama/examples.git
@end example

